  "body": "Ideally, this should be a subcommand like `forge fmt <Options...>`\r\n\r\nRules and settings should be on par with https://github.com/prettier-solidity/prettier-plugin-solidity\r\n\r\n#176 contains a basic design skeleton for how this could look like.\r\n\r\nLike `prettier-solidity`, we'd parse the AST (with [`solang`](https://github.com/hyperledger-labs/solang/tree/main/src/parser)'s parser) then convert all nodes back to text but formatted, according to the configured rules.\r\n\r\n## Tasks left for #176\r\n- [x] Implement `Visitable` for all `solang` AST nodes\r\n- [x] Implement all event handlers in the `Formatter` visitor that then convert a node to text\r\n- [x] Ensure formatting is lossless\r\n- [ ] supports `prettier-solidity` rules\r\n- [x] Add an `fmt` subcommand for the cli app\r\n",
